		<h3>Attack Motion Sweetspot</h3>
		<p>
			Every weapon attack has a sweetspot during its motion: if the attack hits a monster during the sweetspot it will deal full damage, if it hits too early it will deal 30% damage, and if it hits too late it will deal 50%. The early penalty will only apply at yellow sharpness and below, and the late penalty will apply at all sharpness levels. Additionally, Great Sword attacks deal 105% damage instead of 100% if the attack hits in the middle of the blade's length and during the sweetspot of the motion.
		</p>

		<h3>Weapon Reaction Value</h3>
		<p>
			A Blademaster weapon's attack can have one of four different reactions on hitting a monster: bounce, hitslow, hitstop, or normal motion. This Reaction Value is the product of the weapon's sharpness modifier, monster hitzone, and sweetspot.
		</p>
